ENTRY            M0680   20260120   20260302   20260302       M144
SUBENT        M0680001   20260120   20260302   20260302       M144
BIB                 12         55
TITLE      Simultaneous measurement of the photodisintegration
            of 4He in the giant dipole resonance region.
AUTHOR     (T.Shima,S.Naito,Y.Nagai,T.Baba,K.Tamura,T.Takahashi,
            T.Kii,H.Ohgaki,H.Toyokawa)
REFERENCE  (J,PR/C,72,044004,2005)
           #doi:10.1103/PhysRevC.72.044004
           (C,2006CERN,,176,2006) (identical data)
           (J,NP/A,718,23,2003) - conf.proceedings
           #doi:10.1016/S0375-9474(03)00675-4
INSTITUTE  (2JPNOSA,2JPNTIT,2JPNKTO,2JPNAIS)
FACILITY   (ESTRG,2JPNAIS) Electron storage ring TERAS at the
            National Institute of Advanced Industrial Science and
            Technology (AIST)
INC-SOURCE (LCS) Laser Compton scattering.
METHOD     (EXTB,SITA)
SAMPLE     A mixed gas of 80% natural HE 20% CH-4 with a total
            pressure of 1000 Torr.
DETECTOR   (TRD) The 4PI time projection chamber (TPC) provides
            the information of the track shapes and energies of
            the charged particles produced in the reactions.
ANALYSIS   Direct measurement.
COMMENT    The simultaneous measurement of the two-body and
            three-body photodisintegration cross sections of 4He
            has been measured for the first time in the energy
            region from 21.8 to 29.8 MeV using monoenergetic
            pulsed photons and a 4PI time projection chamber
            containing 4He gas as an active target in an
            event-by-event mode. The photon beam was produced via
            the Compton backscattering of laser photons with high
            energy electrons. The 4He(g,p) 3H and 4He(g,n) 3He
            reaction cross sections were found out to increase
            monotonically with energy up to 29.8 MeV, in contrast
            to the result of a recent theoretical calculation
            based on the Lorentz integral transform method that
            predicted a pronounced peak at around 26 - 27 MeV.
            The energy dependence of the obtained 4He(g,n) 3He
            reaction cross section up to 26.5 MeV is marginally
            consistent with a Faddeev-type calculation predicting
            a flat pattern of the excitation function. The
            article C,2006CERN,176,2006 presented in REFERENCE
            included identical data has another title -
            "Photonuclear reactions of light nuclei studied
            with high-intensity real photon beams".
HISTORY    (20060130C) Data were compiled at MSU SINP CDFE by
           V.V.Varlamov.
           (20060130R) Partially data tables were obtained
            from Prof. T.Shima.
           (20060331A) DATA-HEAD in SUBENT 007 and REACTION in
            SUBENT 008 corrected.
           (20100916A) REFERENCE added.
           (20101201A) Typographical mistakes corrected, INC-
            SOURCE = LCS.
           (20111117A) Corrected by V.Varlamov: TITLE, AUTHOR,
            CRITIQUE.
           (20260120U) Corrected by VV and SD: STATUS.
